@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>Welcome to JwtAuthDemoUI</h1>

<p>
    This application demonstrates how to integrate <strong>JWT authentication</strong> 
    into a Blazor WebAssembly frontend. It provides a complete cycle of 
    <em>login</em>, <em>role-based access</em>, and <em>logout</em> functionality.
</p>

<h3>What you can do here:</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Login</strong> with your credentials to receive a secure JWT token.</li>
    <li><strong>Profile Page</strong> shows your username and role from the token claims.</li>
    <li><strong>Admin Only</strong> page demonstrates restricted access for administrators.</li>
    <li><strong>User Only</strong> page demonstrates restricted access for standard users.</li>
    <li><strong>Common Page</strong> is accessible to both Admins and Users.</li>
    <li><strong>Logout</strong> clears your token and resets authentication state.</li>
</ul>

<p>
    Use the navigation menu to explore each page and test how 
    <strong>role-based authorization</strong> works in Blazor.
</p>
